hpicfServiceTunnel.name: hpicfServiceTunnel
hpicfServiceTunnel.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfServiceTunnel.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary objects for managing service tunnels.

hpicfMaxIPv4ServiceTunnels.name: hpicfMaxIPv4ServiceTunnels
hpicfMaxIPv4ServiceTunnels.description: Maximum number of IPv4 service tunnels supported on the device which is a sum of maximum Inspect and Tap tunnels.

hpicfTotalIPv4ServiceTunnels.name: hpicfTotalIPv4ServiceTunnels
hpicfTotalIPv4ServiceTunnels.description: Total number of IPv4 service tunnels configured on the device.This includes both Inspect and Tap tunnels

hpicfMaxInterceptServiceTunnels.name: hpicfMaxInterceptServiceTunnels
hpicfMaxInterceptServiceTunnels.description: Maximum number of Inspect service tunnels supported on the device.

hpicfTotalIPv4InterceptServiceTunnels.name: hpicfTotalIPv4InterceptServiceTunnels
hpicfTotalIPv4InterceptServiceTunnels.description: Total number of IPv4 service tunnels of type Inspect configured on the device.

hpicfMaxIPv4TapServiceTunnels.name: hpicfMaxIPv4TapServiceTunnels
hpicfMaxIPv4TapServiceTunnels.description: Maximum number of IPv4 service tunnels of type Tap supported on the device.

hpicfTotalIPv4TapServiceTunnels.name: hpicfTotalIPv4TapServiceTunnels
hpicfTotalIPv4TapServiceTunnels.description: Total number of IPv4 service tunnels of type Tap configured on the device.

hpicfServiceTunnelTable.name: hpicfServiceTunnelTable
hpicfServiceTunnelTable.description: Table containing information on service tunnels. These are class of IP tunnels that can be used to encapsulate Ethernet frames along with the MAC and VLAN headers.

hpicfServiceTunnelEntry.name: hpicfServiceTunnelEntry
hpicfServiceTunnelEntry.description: An entry containing the information on a particular service tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelType.name: hpicfServiceTunnelType
hpicfServiceTunnelType.description: This object is used to configure the service tunnel type. A value of none(0) indicates that this is not a service tunnel. A value of intercept(1) indicates that the service tunnel type is intercept. Intercept tunnels are to be used by applications that want to intercept and inspect traffic flowing through a device and re-insert traffic back to the device for forwarding after inspection. A value of tap(2) indicates that the service tunnel is of type Tap. Tap tunnels are used by applications that want to mirror traffic flowing through the device.

hpicfServiceTunnelName.name: hpicfServiceTunnelName
hpicfServiceTunnelName.description: This object is used to assign a textual name to the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelIfTable.name: hpicfServiceTunnelIfTable
hpicfServiceTunnelIfTable.description: Table containing information on service tunnels. These are IP tunnels that can be used to encapsulate Ethernet frames along with the MAC and VLAN headers.

hpicfServiceTunnelIfEntry.name: hpicfServiceTunnelIfEntry
hpicfServiceTunnelIfEntry.description: An entry containing the information on a particular service tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelIfMTU.name: hpicfServiceTunnelIfMTU
hpicfServiceTunnelIfMTU.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent or received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceStatus.name: hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceStatus
hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceStatus.description: This object indicates the operational state of the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceDownReason.name: hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceDownReason
hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceDownReason.description: If the tunnelinterface state is DOWN, this object indicates the reason for which it is down.

hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceTruncate.name: hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceTruncate
hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceTruncate.description: Enables partial payloads to be sent on the Tap tunnels in case of MTU violations.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxInvalidKey.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxInvalidKey
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxInvalidKey.description: Number of encapsulated packets to un-configured tunnel interfaces of type Intercept. This is not applicable to Tap tunnels.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxFragmentDrops.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxFragmentDrops
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxFragmentDrops.description: Number of fragmented packets received and dropped on tunnel interface. This is not applicable to Tap tunnels.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxMTUViolationDro.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxMTUViolationDrop
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxMTUViolationDro.description: Number of packets not transmitted on the tunnel interface for MTU violation reasons. This is common to all service tunnel types.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsUnknownSrcMac.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsUnknownSrcMac
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsUnknownSrcMac.description: Number of packets received on tunnel interfaces but dropped because the source MAC address of the frame is not present in the FDB. This is not applicable to Tap tunnels.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsScalarClear.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsScalarClear
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsScalarClear.description: This object clears tunnel statistics when set to TRUE. A GET request for this object always returns FALSE.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfTable.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfTable
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfTable.description: Table containing statistics information on service tunnels. Service Tap tunnels are uni-directional and will not receive packets. Hence the MIB objects for Rx Statistics are not applicable for Tap tunnels and will always be 0.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfEntry.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfEntry
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsIfEntry.description: An entry containing statistics information on a particular service tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxPackets.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxPackets
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxPackets.description: Number of packets received on the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxPackets.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxPackets
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxPackets.description: Number of packets transmitted out of the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxHeartbeat.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxHeartbeat
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsRxHeartbeat.description: Number of heartbeat packets received on the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxHeartbeat.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxHeartbeat
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsTxHeartbeat.description: Number of heartbeat packets transmitted out of the tunnel interface.

hpicfServiceTunnelLastHeartbeatPacketTim.name: hpicfServiceTunnelLastHeartbeatPacketTimestamp
hpicfServiceTunnelLastHeartbeatPacketTim.description: The value of 'SysUpTime' correspondign to last heartbeat packet that was received on this tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsClear.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsClear
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsClear.description: This object clears tunnel interface statistics when set to TRUE. A GET request for this object always returns FALSE.

hpicfServiceTunnelIfUp.name: hpicfServiceTunnelIfUp
hpicfServiceTunnelIfUp.description: An hpicfServiceTunnelIfUp trap is sent when the the hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceStatus object for a tunnel changes from DOWN to UP.

hpicfServiceTunnelIfDown.name: hpicfServiceTunnelIfDown
hpicfServiceTunnelIfDown.description: An hpicfServiceTunnelIfDown trap is sent when the hpicfServiceTunnelInterfaceStatus object for a tunnel changes from UP to DOWN state.

hpicfServiceTunnelCompliance.name: hpicfServiceTunnelCompliance
hpicfServiceTunnelCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the service tunnel MIB.

hpicfServiceScalarsGroup.name: hpicfServiceScalarsGroup
hpicfServiceScalarsGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel.

hpicfServiceScalarsGroup1.name: hpicfServiceScalarsGroup1
hpicfServiceScalarsGroup1.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel.

hpicfServiceScalarsStatsGroup.name: hpicfServiceScalarsStatsGroup
hpicfServiceScalarsStatsGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel statistics.

hpicfServiceTunnelGroup.name: hpicfServiceTunnelGroup
hpicfServiceTunnelGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelGroup1.name: hpicfServiceTunnelGroup1
hpicfServiceTunnelGroup1.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel.

hpicfServiceTunnelStatsGroup.name: hpicfServiceTunnelStatsGroup
hpicfServiceTunnelStatsGroup.description: The collection of objects providing information about the service tunnel statistics.
